cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper proposes a new approach to Datalog evaluation using linear algebraic methods. It is likely to be categorized under cs.DB (databases), as it deals with the evaluation of Datalog programs. It also involves matrix operations, which suggests a possible categorization under cs.LG (machine learning) or cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of this approach for artificial intelligence applications, which could lead to a categorization under cs.AI (artificial intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the time complexity of the approach, which could lead to a categorization under cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing).
